items.name: Biotin Can Distort Lab Tests
items.description: The FDA is warning that high doses of vitamin B7, or biotin, in dietary supplements can interfere with hundreds of common lab tests
items.detail: In some cases, extra biotin causes falsely high results on tests. In others, it causes the results to read as falsely low. Tzhatâ€™s true with some ways to detect a protein called troponin, which rises after heart muscle has been damaged.
